Actually, I want to also check: does the content script get re-injected when the extension is reloaded? In Firefox, content scripts are injected at document start/ready based on the manifest's `run_at`. If the extension is reloaded, content scripts are NOT automatically re-injected into already-loaded pages. They only apply to new page loads. So the only way the content script runs again on the same page is if the page is navigated/reloaded.

So the `window.__tabtamerPatched` guard is for the case where the content script is somehow injected twice (which shouldn't normally happen, but the guard is defensive).

