Actually, looking at the `hibernateIdleTabs` code again:

```js
const lastAccess = _lastAccessTimes[tab.id] || tab.lastAccessed || 0;
if (now - lastAccess < hibernateAfterMs) continue;
```

For the tabs that we DON'T want to discard, we can call `updateLastAccess(tabId)` which sets `_lastAccessTimes[tabId] = Date.now()`.

For tabs we DO want to discard, we just don't call `updateLastAccess()` - and `_lastAccessTimes[tabId]` will be undefined, so `lastAccess` falls back to `tab.lastAccessed || 0`. If `tab.lastAccessed` is also undefined, it's 0, and `now - 0` is huge, exceeding `hibernateAfterMs`. So the tab WILL be discarded.

So the test for discarding idle tabs can work like this:
1. Set up managed group (call `loadManagedGroups()`)
2. Call `updateLastAccess(activeTabId)` for the active tab
3. Don't call anything for the idle tab
4. `hibernateIdleTabs()` will discard the idle tab (since `_lastAccessTimes[idleTabId]` is undefined, falls to 0)

